data.title: Football Commentators Thread (Part 20) - Page 686
data.meta_description: Funny how we all perceive accents and that differently, I've always heard Dempsey as being Irish, right back to when I first saw him as a kid on the boxing on Sky.
data.text:
Amazon's details for next week or so:

Sunday - Leicester V Brighton - Logan, Morrison and Townsend in studio - Drury and Shearer commentating

Tuesday:

Wolves V Chelsea - Thomas, Scholes and J Cole - Mowbray and Upson commentating

Man City V West Brom - Logan, Hargreaves, McManaman and Shearer - Drury and Townsend commentating

Wednesday:

Leicester V Everton - Currie, P Neville and Schmeichel - commentary from Wilson and Morrioson

Arsenal V Southampton - Angus Scott, Campbell and Holland - Tyldesley and Osman commentating

Leeds V Newcastle - Whitaker, Hasselbaink and L Ferdinand - commentary from Proudfoot and Hoddle

Liverpool V Tottenham - Logan, Shearer, Martinez and Crouch - commentary from Champion and McCoist

West Ham V Crystal Palace - Buckland, H Redknapp and J Cole - commentary from McNamara and Ward

Fulham V Brighton - Somers, Jenas and Aluko - commentary from Darke and Upson

Thursday:

Aston Villa V Burnley - Rosenthal, Carney and M Brown - commentary from Tyldesley and Beglin

Sheff Utd V Man Utd - Thomas, Martinez, Scholes and Owen - commentary from Champion and McCoist

Great to see Champion and McCoist used for Livverpool and Man Utd games - although perhaps a surprise Tyldesley isn't doing one of those. We'll have to wait for games 28-30 of course.

Co-commentators look weaker than last year. No Burley or Kilbane, perhaps because of travel restrictions. Not sure about Upson, Osman and especially Clinton Morrison as co-commentators.

Proudfoot instead of Summerton is disappointing and a shame no Derek Rae, again perhaps because of travel complications. The likes of Thierry Henry, Lee Dixon and Gramee Le Saux are notable absentees from last year, with Beglin, Jenas and Hoddle perhaps a bit underused. No Sue Smith, Matt Smith or Pardew either.

Apparently Dempsey was born in London, but Iâ€™ve never been sure if his accent is Irish or not.

Funnily enough when he's commentated before I've seen people on Twitter suggesting he had a broad Norfolk accent. As I always say, for someone who has been involved in football on TV for about thirty years, he does seem a bit of an unknown quantity.
